{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In particular, Piecewise Aggregate Approximation (PAA) [77] and Adaptive Piecewise Constant Approximation (APCA) [24] segment a vector into equal or variable length segments, respectively, and summarize each segment with its mean value.",
    "Extended APCA (EAPCA) [146] improves upon APCA by using both the mean and standard deviation to summarize each segment.",
    "Symbolic Aggregate Approximation (SAX) [87] transforms a vector using PAA and discretizes the values using a scalar quantizer.",
    "Deep Embedding Approximation (DEA) learns summarizations using the SEAnet deep neural network [145].",
    "Tree-based indexes organize the data using a tree structure and have been the method of choice for exact vector search for data series and generic high-dimensional vectors [16, 25, 27, 28, 39, 48, 62, 82, 90, 111-113, 122, 145, 146, 148, 157, 166]."
  ],
